transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Charles, how are you buddy?

Speaker 1: I'm good. How about yourself?

Speaker 2: I'm all right. So I, um, my name is Mr. Ding.

Speaker 1: I'm trying to cancel a prescription that I have signed up about a month ago.

Speaker 2: Okay. And you're in Liverpool, New York, right?

Speaker 1: That's correct.

Speaker 2: Gotcha. Are you overstocked right now and don't need any for a while?

Speaker 1: No. Yeah, I'm okay. The medicine doesn't work, so I'm going to go to my doctor.

Speaker 2: Gotcha. Okay. Um, if you'd like, um, it looks like you're only getting 25 milligrams.

Speaker 1: I can send you a sample of 100 milligrams and see if that does anything for you.

Speaker 2: I won't charge you a dime on it.

Speaker 1: We obviously want to make sure that you have a pleasant experience with us.

Speaker 2: Um, so I can up the dosage and then send you a different version of the AGV that's made in our France factory.

Speaker 1: It's a lot more potent. Um, so I can send you that for free.

Speaker 2: I'll pause everything for the time being.

Speaker 1: Um, that way you're able to try it and then call us and let us know, uh, what the final deal is.

Speaker 2: Yeah, just, just, just pause everything for now.

Speaker 1: Just cancel it until I get back to you, but you could do that, yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay. I'll send you that and then I'll pause everything from now until June, okay?

Speaker 1: Alrighty. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay. Sounds good. These ones will have the number 100 pressed onto them, okay?

Speaker 1: Alrighty.

Speaker 2: Okay. Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too. Thank you. Bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye-bye.
